The long-awaited murder trial of soccer star #SenzoMeyiwa is expected to begin on Monday in the High Court. For more, Slindelo Masikane speaks to AfriForum's Head of Private Prosecution Unit #GerrieNel. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former Bafana Bafana captain Senzo Meyiwa’s murder trial is set to begin on Monday in the High Court. The five accused are facing charges of murder, attempted murder, armed robbery, possession of firearms without a licence, and the possession of ammunition. It's been eight years since the shocking murder of Meyiwa. Watch the video above for more details.